OL,6,FCommenting on the report, Welsh
OL,7,FLiberal Democrat Westminster
OL,8,Fspokesperson David Chadwick said:
OL,9,F"There are practical, fair
OL,10,Falternatives on the table that would
OL,11,Fclose loopholes exploited by large
OL,12,Fmultinationals, without inflicting the
OL,13,Fdevastating harm this policy would
OL,14,Fcause to our rural economy and
OL,15,Fcommunities."
OL,17,FKath Whitrow, a sheep farmer in
OL,18,FGlynneath, chairs a hill farmers board
OL,19,Fof the National Farmers Union Cymru.
